{"key":"post-13685842","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13685842</id>\n<content>In my shiitake farm, there's a direct correlation between fruit size and how far from the lights each block is.&amp;nbsp; My blocks on the 'darker' shelves produce less than half the amount of product as blocks on the 'bright' shelves with the LED spotlights shining on them.&amp;nbsp; This phenomena has been well known for years.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I know of no scientific document anywhere that says mushrooms need light to &quot;know which way to grow&quot;.&amp;nbsp; That's something some stoner came up with and it keeps getting repeated, making noobs think it's correct.&amp;nbsp; Mushrooms use light as a source of energy.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13686093</next>\n<prev>13685802</prev>\n<first>13684454</first>\n<last>13720036</last>\n<when>1293376629</when>\n<utime>12/26/10 05:17 PM</utime>\n</post>"}